LOKOJA  – MultiChoice Nigeria, has unveiled GOtv brand in Lokoja, Kogi state capital, with the promise to move the teeming unemployed youths out of poverty and to unite families through programming and contents. Executive Director Sales, Akin Salu, while unveiling the brand on Saturday in Lokoja, said GOtv packages is to enhance family union through unhindered access to multiple channels with programmes and deep contents. According to him, “GOtv is a family affairs, with something for everyone.” He said the product offerings include Jolly, Marks and Super, which hitherto cost N9.500, have been sliced to N6900 to take care of every customer. He said: “The brand will also enhance economic fortunes of the unemployed youths and adults who wants to increase their wealth by engaging in marketing the product thereby reducing poverty facing the country. “To this end, over two hundred branded stores have been established in Lokoja, while over hundred young boys and girls have been recruited as canvassers in order to improve their lives and to enable customers have easy access to the products. Akin Salu disclosed that GOtv has over hundred channels with relevant programmes to enhance entertainment, education, sports. He boasted that GOtv has become the industry leader in its short period of operations. He assured the customers in Lokoja that the company will continue to work harder to meet their satisfaction. POLL The Executive head of sales promises to keep the people entertained, grow their income through active participation and assured of entering other geo- political zones of the country. In his remark, the representative of Maigeri of Lokoja, Alhaji Alih Lawal, commended the management for choosing Lokoja to birth product in North Central Zone.